Path: godot/classes/class_textedit.rst
Summary: This chunk lists all the properties of the TextEdit node, including their types and default values.

* autowrap_mode (AutowrapMode): The autowrap mode to use. See TextServer.AutowrapMode. Default: 3.
* backspace_deletes_composite_character_enabled (bool): If false, backspace will not be able to delete composite characters. Default: false.
* caret_blink (bool): If true, the caret (text cursor) blinks. Default: false.
* caret_blink_interval (float): The caret's blink interval, in seconds. Default: 0.65.
* caret_draw_when_editable_disabled (bool): If true, the caret is visible when editable is disabled. Default: false.
* caret_mid_grapheme (bool): If true, the caret can be positioned at the middle of a grapheme. Default: false.
* caret_move_on_right_click (bool): If true, the caret will be moved to the clicked position on right-click. Default: true.
* caret_multiple (bool): If true, multiple carets are allowed. Default: true.
* caret_type (CaretType): The type of caret to use. Default: 0.
* context_menu_enabled (bool): If true, a right-click context menu is enabled. Default: true.
* custom_word_separators (String): Custom word separators to use for word navigation. Default: "".
* deselect_on_focus_loss_enabled (bool): If true, the selection is lost when the TextEdit node loses focus. Default: true.
* drag_and_drop_selection_enabled (bool): If true, selected text can be dragged to another position to move it. Default: true.
* draw_control_chars (bool): If true, control characters are displayed. Default: false.
* draw_spaces (bool): If true, spaces are displayed. Default: false.
* draw_tabs (bool): If true, tabs are displayed. Default: false.
* editable (bool): If false, existing text cannot be modified and new text cannot be inserted. Default: true.
* emoji_menu_enabled (bool): If true, the emoji picker is enabled. Default: true.
* empty_selection_clipboard_enabled (bool): If true, allows copying and cutting when no text is selected. Default: true.
* focus_mode (FocusMode): The focus mode for the control. Default: 2 (overrides Control).
* highlight_all_occurrences (bool): If true, all occurrences of the selected text will be highlighted. Default: false.
* highlight_current_line (bool): If true, the current line is highlighted. Default: false.
* indent_wrapped_lines (bool): If true, wrapped lines are indented to the same level as the first line. Default: false.
* language (String): The language code used for text shaping. Default: "".
* middle_mouse_paste_enabled (bool): If true, the selected text will be pasted on middle mouse click. Default: true.
* minimap_draw (bool): If true, a minimap is shown. Default: false.
* minimap_width (int): The width of the minimap, in pixels. Default: 80.
* mouse_default_cursor_shape (CursorShape): The default cursor shape for this control. Default: 1 (overrides Control).
* placeholder_text (String): Text to display when the TextEdit is empty. Default: "".
* scroll_fit_content_height (bool): If true, the editor will automatically adjust its height to fit the text. Default: false.
* scroll_fit_content_width (bool): If true, the editor will automatically adjust its width to fit the text. Default: false.
* scroll_horizontal (int): The horizontal scroll value. Default: 0.
* scroll_past_end_of_file (bool): If true, allows scrolling past the end of the file. Default: false.
* scroll_smooth (bool): If true, smooth scrolling is enabled. Default: false.
* scroll_v_scroll_speed (float): The vertical scroll speed. Default: 80.0.
* scroll_vertical (float): The vertical scroll value. Default: 0.0.
* selecting_enabled (bool): If true, text can be selected. Default: true.
* shortcut_keys_enabled (bool): If true, shortcut keys for this control are enabled. Default: true.
* structured_text_bidi_override (StructuredTextParser): The bidi override for structured text. Default: 0.
* structured_text_bidi_override_options (Array): Options for bidi override. Default: [].
* syntax_highlighter (SyntaxHighlighter): The SyntaxHighlighter to use.
* tab_input_mode (bool): If true, pressing the Tab key will insert a tab character. If false, it will change focus. Default: true.
* text (String): The text content of the editor. Default: "".
* text_direction (TextDirection): The base direction of the text. Default: 0.
* use_custom_word_separators (bool): If true, custom word separators are used. Default: false.
* use_default_word_separators (bool): If true, default word separators are used. Default: true.
* virtual_keyboard_enabled (bool): If true, the virtual keyboard is supported. Default: true.
* virtual_keyboard_show_on_focus (bool): If true, the virtual keyboard is shown when the editor is focused. Default: true.
* wrap_mode (LineWrappingMode): The line wrapping mode. Default: 0.
---CHUNK---
